1
00:00:36,724 --> 00:00:38,643
Boss! Boss!

2
00:00:40,645 --> 00:00:42,647
- What is that?
- Hey, you masked bastard.

3
00:00:42,730 --> 00:00:44,106
Now you're dead meat.

4
00:00:44,231 --> 00:00:46,067
Hey, attack him!

5
00:00:46,609 --> 00:00:47,943
Attack him, quickly!

6
00:00:48,027 --> 00:00:49,945
Hey, hurry up!

7
00:00:58,245 --> 00:00:59,246
What the hell?

8
00:01:12,093 --> 00:01:13,761
This bastard. Hey, hey, get up.

9
00:01:13,844 --> 00:01:15,096
Hey, you bastard! Get over here!

10
00:01:15,179 --> 00:01:16,639
Huh? Come on!

11
00:01:17,181 --> 00:01:18,849
Hey, he's alive. Damn it.

12
00:01:23,562 --> 00:01:24,689
The bathroom.

13
00:01:25,022 --> 00:01:26,816
Hey, there's big trouble in the bathroom.

14
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:29,276
- Get to the bathroom, now!
- You bastard!

15
00:01:36,617 --> 00:01:37,618
Kang-sik!

16
00:01:40,871 --> 00:01:41,872
Boss.

17
00:01:44,542 --> 00:01:45,543
Hey!

18
00:01:45,626 --> 00:01:46,627
Go!

19
00:01:54,093 --> 00:01:55,094
Hey, lock the door!

20
00:02:00,349 --> 00:02:01,350
You!

21
00:02:39,764 --> 00:02:40,931
In-gu!

22
00:03:27,770 --> 00:03:28,771
You hear that?

23
00:03:28,854 --> 00:03:31,065
It means you're a dead man.

24
00:03:33,692 --> 00:03:34,693
Damn it.

25
00:04:06,475 --> 00:04:08,227
- What?
- What the?

26
00:04:08,310 --> 00:04:11,355
- Turn on the lights!
- What the hell?

27
00:04:11,522 --> 00:04:13,983
- Where did he go?
- Hey, find him, quick!

28
00:04:14,066 --> 00:04:15,359
Find him, now!

29
00:04:57,026 --> 00:04:58,319
ORAN CHINESE RESTAURANT

30
00:04:58,402 --> 00:04:59,570
EPISODE 4

31
00:05:18,339 --> 00:05:19,590
Where have you been?

32
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,634
You weren't answering your phone.
Ho-myeong.

33
00:05:21,926 --> 00:05:23,719
It's an emergency, so be quiet...

34
00:05:25,679 --> 00:05:27,389
What happened to your face? Are you hurt?

35
00:05:27,514 --> 00:05:30,100
I just fell off my motorcycle.

36
00:05:31,018 --> 00:05:32,436
- I need some rest.
- Good grief.

37
00:05:32,811 --> 00:05:33,854
I need to talk to you.

38
00:05:34,563 --> 00:05:35,731
You two can head home first.

39
00:05:35,814 --> 00:05:38,150
All right, then. You two wrap
things up and come along.

40
00:05:38,442 --> 00:05:39,985
- Okay, let's go.
- Hold on.

41
00:05:40,152 --> 00:05:42,112
We should hear what happened too.

42
00:05:42,905 --> 00:05:43,906
We need to go now.

43
00:05:43,989 --> 00:05:44,990
It's time to go.

44
00:05:45,074 --> 00:05:46,075
Let's go.

45
00:05:58,754 --> 00:05:59,755
Talk to me.

46
00:06:01,048 --> 00:06:04,093
You haven't answered your phone all day.

47
00:06:04,718 --> 00:06:06,303
So why are you crawling in now,
looking like that?

48
00:06:08,472 --> 00:06:09,765
I was out on a delivery...

49
00:06:10,474 --> 00:06:13,936
I crashed my bike, and when I came to,
it was already this late.

50
00:06:14,061 --> 00:06:15,145
Where?

51
00:06:15,479 --> 00:06:17,648
Mr. Kim said he drove
all around the neighborhood

52
00:06:17,773 --> 00:06:19,066
and didn't see you.

53
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:20,985
Let's talk about it later.

54
00:06:21,986 --> 00:06:22,987
Tell me before you go.

55
00:06:23,195 --> 00:06:25,322
- Can't you see I'm hurt?
- Exactly.

56
00:06:25,406 --> 00:06:27,825
Where were you
and what were you doing to get so hurt...

57
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:29,743
that you didn't go pick up Ji-woo?

58
00:06:32,997 --> 00:06:33,998
Don't tell me...

59
00:06:34,498 --> 00:06:35,916
you just remembered now?

60
00:06:37,042 --> 00:06:39,294
Are you out of your mind? Ji-woo...

61
00:06:40,587 --> 00:06:42,131
That six-year-old boy...

62
00:06:42,214 --> 00:06:44,008
Because you never showed up

63
00:06:44,091 --> 00:06:47,177
he walked home by himself for 30 minutes.

64
00:06:47,261 --> 00:06:48,303
Is Ji-woo okay?

65
00:06:48,387 --> 00:06:49,430
And that makes it okay?

66
00:06:49,888 --> 00:06:51,432
What if on his way home alone...

67
00:06:52,474 --> 00:06:53,767
he'd gotten into an accident?

68
00:06:54,143 --> 00:06:56,520
What would you have done
if he'd gotten lost?

69
00:07:00,607 --> 00:07:01,608
I'm sorry.

70
00:07:02,026 --> 00:07:03,027
You're sorry?

71
00:07:03,277 --> 00:07:04,278
For what?

72
00:07:04,445 --> 00:07:06,780
Why are you always like this, huh?

73
00:07:06,864 --> 00:07:08,866
Why can't you just tell me straight?

74
00:07:12,619 --> 00:07:14,788
You're just going to clam up like that?

75
00:08:00,793 --> 00:08:07,049
7 YEARS AGO

76
00:08:10,052 --> 00:08:11,053
Seong-won, I...

77
00:08:11,762 --> 00:08:13,097
I'm getting married.

78
00:08:13,180 --> 00:08:15,849
O-ran's... pregnant.

79
00:08:16,642 --> 00:08:18,894
Hey, you idiot!
How could you be so careless?

80
00:08:19,144 --> 00:08:20,312
Is this really the time
for you to get married?

81
00:08:20,562 --> 00:08:23,315
- What about the operation?
- Getting married won't change anything.

82
00:08:23,398 --> 00:08:25,400
My revenge on Han Gyeong-wook,
finding Bulgae...

83
00:08:25,484 --> 00:08:26,735
everything will proceed without a hitch.

84
00:08:26,819 --> 00:08:28,362
You think it's as easy as it sounds?

85
00:08:29,696 --> 00:08:31,865
What are you going to do when the time
comes to choose between them?

86
00:08:31,949 --> 00:08:33,450
Why are you being so negative?

87
00:08:33,534 --> 00:08:34,618
I can do both.

88
00:08:35,202 --> 00:08:36,662
Jeez, Ho-myeong.

89
00:08:36,912 --> 00:08:38,372
Do you know why I never got married?

90
00:08:38,455 --> 00:08:39,456
I thought it was because you couldn't.

91
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:43,168
I've also spent my life

92
00:08:43,252 --> 00:08:46,505
thinking a family would just get
in the way of the operation.

93
00:08:46,964 --> 00:08:48,173
But, no.

94
00:08:49,716 --> 00:08:52,511
The moment Oran told me about the baby,
I realized something.

95
00:08:53,512 --> 00:08:55,013
That for my family...

96
00:08:56,557 --> 00:08:58,225
there's nothing I wouldn't do.

97
00:09:11,196 --> 00:09:12,656
Hey, President Yoo.

98
00:09:13,073 --> 00:09:14,241
Are you okay?

99
00:09:14,324 --> 00:09:15,325
You feeling all right?

100
00:09:15,826 --> 00:09:17,411
How did you know I was here?

101
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:19,872
Come on. Of course I had to visit.

102
00:09:19,955 --> 00:09:21,790
A coworker got hurt.

103
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:24,251
But...

104
00:09:24,835 --> 00:09:26,086
this isn't a private room.

105
00:09:30,674 --> 00:09:31,842
Could you move aside?

106
00:09:34,803 --> 00:09:36,555
Who the hell are you
to tell a patient to move?

107
00:09:37,848 --> 00:09:39,516
- Hey!
- Damn it.

108
00:09:41,435 --> 00:09:42,436
Everyone, get out.

109
00:09:42,519 --> 00:09:43,520
Yes, Boss.

110
00:09:43,812 --> 00:09:44,813
All of you, get out.

111
00:09:44,897 --> 00:09:45,898
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

112
00:09:45,981 --> 00:09:47,024
Out, out, out, out.

113
00:09:56,241 --> 00:09:58,202
You're more hurt than I thought.

114
00:09:59,953 --> 00:10:01,288
That son of a bitch.

115
00:10:01,371 --> 00:10:03,248
I heard it was just one guy
who did all this.

116
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:05,000
Is this for real?

117
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:06,084
The almighty Ingu Sect?

118
00:10:06,168 --> 00:10:08,921
Stay out of what happens on my turf.

119
00:10:09,087 --> 00:10:10,088
No way.

120
00:10:10,255 --> 00:10:12,382
I'd love to stay out of it.
But you know how it is.

121
00:10:12,674 --> 00:10:14,927
The day after tomorrow,
I have to report to Chief Han

122
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:17,137
on the Yeongseon Island project.

123
00:10:17,596 --> 00:10:20,641
All right, the security room incident,
that's number one. And...

124
00:10:21,099 --> 00:10:22,267
this one is number two.

125
00:10:22,601 --> 00:10:25,187
With all this trouble
happening with Heaven Capital

126
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:27,940
I'm not quite sure what stance to take.
It's putting me in a tough spot.

127
00:10:28,148 --> 00:10:29,149
You know?

128
00:10:30,776 --> 00:10:31,818
Hey, Chairman Do.

129
00:10:31,985 --> 00:10:33,904
You think I can't clean up
a mess like this?

130
00:10:34,947 --> 00:10:36,365
Watch your mouth.

131
00:10:37,366 --> 00:10:38,742
Keep running your mouth like that...

132
00:10:40,118 --> 00:10:41,119
and you'll end up dead.

133
00:10:46,083 --> 00:10:48,293
I know, I know.

134
00:10:48,835 --> 00:10:51,672
I know exactly
what you're capable of, President Yoo.

135
00:10:51,755 --> 00:10:53,590
That's why we're in the same boat.

136
00:10:53,966 --> 00:10:57,469
As long as this business goes smoothly

137
00:10:57,552 --> 00:10:58,929
I have no problem.

138
00:10:59,972 --> 00:11:00,973
No problem.

139
00:11:01,974 --> 00:11:02,975
Oh.

140
00:11:03,475 --> 00:11:04,476
Vitamins.

141
00:11:04,559 --> 00:11:05,560
Please.

142
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,897
Make sure you take these vitamins

143
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,441
and get well soon.

144
00:11:11,525 --> 00:11:12,526
Get better.

145
00:11:12,609 --> 00:11:13,610
Goodbye.

146
00:11:14,820 --> 00:11:16,905
We'll talk business next time.

147
00:11:17,572 --> 00:11:18,573
Bye.

148
00:11:19,199 --> 00:11:20,200
See you.

149
00:11:26,248 --> 00:11:27,249
Why...

150
00:11:28,709 --> 00:11:30,711
What is it, boss?

151
00:11:30,794 --> 00:11:33,088
- What is it?
- Go bring me that Masked Bastard.

152
00:11:33,714 --> 00:11:34,715
Boss, I...

153
00:11:35,299 --> 00:11:36,883
How am I supposed to find him
when we don't know who he is?

154
00:11:38,302 --> 00:11:40,470
Hey, you moron! Isn't it obvious?

155
00:11:40,554 --> 00:11:42,347
The guy who took down
our Ingu Sect all by himself

156
00:11:42,514 --> 00:11:44,141
who else holds a grudge against us?

157
00:11:44,224 --> 00:11:45,934
Who else could it be
but that Martial Arts Master

158
00:11:46,018 --> 00:11:47,394
we beat up and took his house deed from?

159
00:11:47,477 --> 00:11:49,146
But his fighting style...

160
00:11:49,229 --> 00:11:50,605
it felt different
from the masked guy's. Right?

161
00:11:50,689 --> 00:11:52,858
- Yeah.
- Forget his damn fighting style

162
00:11:52,941 --> 00:11:54,234
and just go get him!

163
00:11:54,359 --> 00:11:55,360
We'll know...

164
00:11:55,444 --> 00:11:56,778
- We'll get him
- When we beat it out of him! Damn it!

165
00:11:58,071 --> 00:11:59,156
I'll get him.

166
00:11:59,364 --> 00:12:00,365
Damn it.

167
00:12:03,952 --> 00:12:07,122
SEOUL METROPOLITAN POLICE AGENCY

168
00:12:15,339 --> 00:12:16,340
Hey.

169
00:12:17,090 --> 00:12:18,884
- Did you look into what I asked?
- Yes.

170
00:12:19,509 --> 00:12:21,345
The most important part you need to see

171
00:12:21,428 --> 00:12:22,429
is on page three.

172
00:12:24,973 --> 00:12:27,267
This is the Hwasan Sect's
organizational chart from ten years ago.

173
00:12:27,434 --> 00:12:29,186
At the time, the boss, Hwang Hwa-san

174
00:12:29,269 --> 00:12:31,521
was charged with soliciting
the murder of Kwon Soon-bok

175
00:12:31,605 --> 00:12:33,357
and after he received a life sentence,
the sect fell apart.

176
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:35,067
The second-in-command, Gang Beom-ryong

177
00:12:35,150 --> 00:12:36,526
suddenly disappeared without a trace.

178
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:37,694
So he's missing?

179
00:12:38,111 --> 00:12:39,112
It's hard to say.

180
00:12:39,321 --> 00:12:42,074
In any case, there's no record
of any activity after that.

181
00:12:42,282 --> 00:12:43,867
And so, naturally

182
00:12:43,950 --> 00:12:45,702
the number three, Yoo In-gu

183
00:12:45,786 --> 00:12:47,829
ended up taking over
the entire Hwasan Sect.

184
00:12:48,330 --> 00:12:50,082
He even changed the gang's name from the
Hwasan Sect

185
00:12:50,165 --> 00:12:51,249
to the Ingu Sect

186
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:53,293
and expanded their influence.

187
00:12:53,377 --> 00:12:55,045
Yoo In-gu.

188
00:12:55,796 --> 00:12:57,047
Have his whereabouts been confirmed?

189
00:12:57,130 --> 00:12:58,924
Yes. It's on the last page.

190
00:13:00,884 --> 00:13:02,844
It's called Heaven Capital
on Yeongseon Island

191
00:13:03,011 --> 00:13:04,179
located inside Heaven Casino.

192
00:13:04,262 --> 00:13:06,056
His most recent move was registering it

193
00:13:06,139 --> 00:13:07,432
as a private lending company.

194
00:13:07,516 --> 00:13:08,517
Wait a minute.

195
00:13:08,892 --> 00:13:09,976
Did you say Yeongseon Island?

196
00:13:10,268 --> 00:13:12,187
Yes. Is there a problem?

197
00:13:16,274 --> 00:13:17,984
YEONGSEON ISLAND

198
00:13:20,904 --> 00:13:22,614
Yeongseon Island.

199
00:13:23,448 --> 00:13:24,491
So...

200
00:13:24,574 --> 00:13:25,700
you came back empty-handed?

201
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:29,162
See? This is why I told you
not to go off on your own.

202
00:13:29,287 --> 00:13:32,207
By the way,
the jerky factory seemed suspicious.

203
00:13:32,666 --> 00:13:34,584
- I thought we should hit it...
- Stop it!

204
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,169
Don't you dare go there alone.

205
00:13:36,253 --> 00:13:37,379
Why not?

206
00:13:37,462 --> 00:13:38,547
I can handle it.

207
00:13:38,630 --> 00:13:39,631
Ho-myeong.

208
00:13:39,714 --> 00:13:41,174
You're not the man you used to be.

209
00:13:41,258 --> 00:13:43,135
You need to face reality.

210
00:13:43,677 --> 00:13:45,679
If you get hurt,
what will you tell your family?

211
00:13:46,513 --> 00:13:48,515
You know that Prosecutor Gang I mentioned?

212
00:13:48,890 --> 00:13:50,934
I think we're just about to entangle her.

213
00:13:51,309 --> 00:13:52,894
So until then, just lay low

214
00:13:52,978 --> 00:13:54,479
and go score some points with your wife.

215
00:13:56,398 --> 00:13:58,066
What's with the sudden advice?

216
00:13:58,483 --> 00:13:59,818
It's not like you're a marriage counselor.

217
00:14:00,277 --> 00:14:02,529
I just hate seeing you
so down in the dumps.

218
00:14:03,029 --> 00:14:04,489
Didn't you say you could handle both?

219
00:14:07,993 --> 00:14:09,119
So just do that and lay low.

220
00:14:09,578 --> 00:14:11,288
And absolutely no acting
on your own. Got it?

221
00:14:11,538 --> 00:14:12,539
I'm hanging up.

222
00:14:29,222 --> 00:14:30,265
Did you find anything?

223
00:14:30,348 --> 00:14:31,349
Yes.

224
00:14:32,309 --> 00:14:33,560
The masked assailant...

225
00:14:33,643 --> 00:14:34,978
It seems President Yoo's men

226
00:14:35,061 --> 00:14:36,563
are desperately looking for him.

227
00:14:37,856 --> 00:14:41,026
The rumor is he's the one who caused
the problem in the security office.

228
00:14:41,359 --> 00:14:43,028
In any case,
he's clearly not your average guy.

229
00:14:43,195 --> 00:14:45,030
He single-handedly
wiped out the Ingu Sect.

230
00:14:45,113 --> 00:14:46,615
Of course he's not average.

231
00:14:46,907 --> 00:14:48,074
Follow up on that

232
00:14:48,158 --> 00:14:49,868
in more detail.

233
00:14:49,951 --> 00:14:50,994
- Understood.
- Also.

234
00:14:51,119 --> 00:14:53,413
Did you look into that jerky business
I mentioned?

235
00:14:53,788 --> 00:14:55,665
They're disguising drugs from China

236
00:14:55,749 --> 00:14:57,834
as beef jerky and distributing them.

237
00:14:58,001 --> 00:14:59,211
Besides our casino

238
00:14:59,294 --> 00:15:02,088
they have a pretty solid
distribution network set up nationwide.

239
00:15:02,547 --> 00:15:05,008
Goodness... Well, I'll be.

240
00:15:06,301 --> 00:15:07,302
Let's see.

241
00:15:07,385 --> 00:15:08,970
The monthly volume is...

242
00:15:09,054 --> 00:15:10,347
REPORT ON YOO IN-GU
AND COMPANY'S DRUG TRAFFICKING

243
00:15:11,139 --> 00:15:12,140
ESTIMATED MONTHLY DISTRIBUTION VOLUME
50KG

244
00:15:12,224 --> 00:15:13,808
Fifty kilograms.

245
00:15:14,184 --> 00:15:15,810
Wow. And the revenue...

246
00:15:16,686 --> 00:15:17,854
Ten, one hundred thousand,
one million, ten million...

247
00:15:19,105 --> 00:15:20,106
Fifteen billion won.

248
00:15:22,692 --> 00:15:24,444
Man, this Yoo In-gu.

249
00:15:25,237 --> 00:15:27,864
He's got a better head
for business than I thought.

250
00:15:27,948 --> 00:15:29,866
To think he built such a cash cow.

251
00:15:31,034 --> 00:15:32,118
What should we do?

252
00:15:32,744 --> 00:15:34,120
This jerky business...

253
00:15:34,412 --> 00:15:37,290
There could be some serious synergy
if we link it to our casino.

254
00:15:37,374 --> 00:15:38,917
If we passed it around the VIP rooms

255
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,168
it could be very lucrative.

256
00:15:40,252 --> 00:15:41,253
This...

257
00:15:41,753 --> 00:15:43,004
There's no reason not to do it, is there?

258
00:15:46,841 --> 00:15:47,842
Let's see.

259
00:15:48,218 --> 00:15:50,554
So all we have to do
is get rid of President Yoo

260
00:15:50,637 --> 00:15:52,013
and we'll be all set.

261
00:15:54,182 --> 00:15:56,309
But making an open move...

262
00:15:56,726 --> 00:15:58,228
is a bit risky.

263
00:15:58,895 --> 00:16:00,146
Do you have a plan?

264
00:16:00,230 --> 00:16:01,940
The enemy's gates down.

265
00:16:02,315 --> 00:16:04,109
but only from the inside.

266
00:16:04,568 --> 00:16:05,735
What does that mean?

267
00:16:06,945 --> 00:16:09,990
The gates of an enemy's fortress
can only be opened from the inside.

268
00:16:10,365 --> 00:16:12,409
Let's find a gatekeeper
who'll throw the gates

269
00:16:12,826 --> 00:16:14,035
wide open for us.

270
00:16:20,792 --> 00:16:22,794
Damn it.

271
00:16:25,088 --> 00:16:26,298
Hey, you find anything?

272
00:16:26,464 --> 00:16:27,549
Boss.

273
00:16:27,632 --> 00:16:28,758
Looks like he already took off.

274
00:16:29,217 --> 00:16:31,261
Yeah, it sure looks like it. Damn it.

275
00:16:31,970 --> 00:16:33,638
Where the hell
are we supposed to find him?

276
00:16:34,389 --> 00:16:35,390
Hey, Boss!

277
00:16:35,473 --> 00:16:36,891
- Look at this.
- What is it?

278
00:16:37,350 --> 00:16:38,560
Remember Martial Arts Master?

279
00:16:38,768 --> 00:16:40,145
He said he worked at an office, didn't he?

280
00:16:41,563 --> 00:16:44,190
I'm just an ordinary office worker.

281
00:16:44,524 --> 00:16:46,610
Just... an office worker.

282
00:16:48,987 --> 00:16:51,281
Well, look at the brains on this one.

283
00:16:51,406 --> 00:16:53,658
Hey, pull up the address for this company.

284
00:16:53,742 --> 00:16:54,868
- Got it?
- Right away, sir.

285
00:16:54,951 --> 00:16:57,120
Let's move. Come on, boys, let's go!

286
00:16:57,203 --> 00:16:58,913
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

287
00:17:05,128 --> 00:17:07,088
Buying this is our little
secret from Mom, okay?

288
00:17:07,714 --> 00:17:08,965
I know.

289
00:17:09,049 --> 00:17:10,675
You keep it a secret too, Dad.

290
00:17:14,262 --> 00:17:15,805
I'm sorry about yesterday.

291
00:17:16,264 --> 00:17:17,641
I made you walk home by yourself.

292
00:17:18,475 --> 00:17:19,517
But, Dad...

293
00:17:19,768 --> 00:17:21,102
Why didn't you come yesterday?

294
00:17:21,603 --> 00:17:23,188
Did you have too many deliveries?

295
00:17:32,947 --> 00:17:33,948
Well...

296
00:17:35,116 --> 00:17:37,410
You know your favorite, Masked Racer?

297
00:17:37,827 --> 00:17:39,871
He has to go right away
when he gets a call, right?

298
00:17:41,581 --> 00:17:42,749
Well, Dad also

299
00:17:43,124 --> 00:17:44,626
got called to action yesterday, too.

300
00:17:45,710 --> 00:17:48,588
You got called to fight bad guys, too?

301
00:17:49,964 --> 00:17:52,008
Whoa, that's so cool.

302
00:17:54,094 --> 00:17:55,637
This is a secret from Mom, too.

303
00:17:55,804 --> 00:17:56,805
Why?

304
00:17:57,263 --> 00:17:59,599
You should've told Mom
you were on a mission.

305
00:18:00,058 --> 00:18:01,601
Mom's really angry.

306
00:18:02,268 --> 00:18:04,979
- Really?
- Grandpa said

307
00:18:05,271 --> 00:18:07,524
that she won't get over it
easily this time.

308
00:18:11,027 --> 00:18:13,863
Dad, I asked I-seo

309
00:18:14,322 --> 00:18:16,616
and she said there's a way
to calm Mom down.

310
00:18:17,909 --> 00:18:18,910
What is it?

311
00:18:19,577 --> 00:18:21,204
No matter how mad she gets

312
00:18:21,287 --> 00:18:23,289
if you compliment her, give her a gift

313
00:18:23,498 --> 00:18:25,333
and take her on a date,
she'll get over it.

314
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:27,127
- A date?
- Dad.

315
00:18:27,877 --> 00:18:29,170
Do you see that?

316
00:18:31,715 --> 00:18:33,675
MASKED RACER'S GREAT ADVENTURE

317
00:18:40,557 --> 00:18:41,558
Oh, my back.

318
00:18:45,270 --> 00:18:47,897
Jeez, where did that guy go now?

319
00:18:57,490 --> 00:18:58,908
Yeongseon Food?

320
00:19:03,246 --> 00:19:05,373
YEONGSEON FOOD

321
00:19:07,208 --> 00:19:08,960
- Hey, get him!
- Get him!

322
00:19:09,043 --> 00:19:10,962
- What do you think you're doing?
- Get in there!

323
00:19:12,046 --> 00:19:14,299
Whoa, hold on there! Just a second.

324
00:19:15,091 --> 00:19:16,551
Hey, it's all right. Come on.

325
00:19:16,634 --> 00:19:17,635
- Come over here.
- Me?

326
00:19:17,719 --> 00:19:19,095
It's all right.

327
00:19:20,305 --> 00:19:21,598
It's fine.

328
00:19:22,182 --> 00:19:23,183
Come here.

329
00:19:23,892 --> 00:19:27,061
- I just want to ask you something, okay?
- Okay...

330
00:19:27,353 --> 00:19:30,482
That guy, Bong Je-sun, works here, right?

331
00:19:32,025 --> 00:19:33,234
Where might that punk be?

332
00:19:33,359 --> 00:19:34,819
PAYSTUB
MANAGER BONG JE-SUN

333
00:19:35,403 --> 00:19:36,404
Manager Bong?

334
00:19:37,113 --> 00:19:38,948
Yeah, Manager Bong.

335
00:19:40,241 --> 00:19:42,035
So where is he? You don't know?

336
00:19:42,327 --> 00:19:43,620
He should be in the factory

337
00:19:43,703 --> 00:19:45,580
on the second floor right now.

338
00:19:45,830 --> 00:19:46,998
Second floor factory? Where is it?

339
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:49,334
Over there.

340
00:19:51,211 --> 00:19:52,837
Hey, it's the second floor!
Let's go, hurry!

341
00:19:52,921 --> 00:19:53,922
Yes, sir, yes!

342
00:19:54,047 --> 00:19:55,298
Hey! Second floor.

343
00:20:00,595 --> 00:20:01,596
Move it!

344
00:20:10,438 --> 00:20:11,439
Manager Bong!

345
00:20:17,612 --> 00:20:19,864
Manager Bong! What are you doing here?

346
00:20:19,948 --> 00:20:21,741
People were saying
the bathroom was too dirty.

347
00:20:21,825 --> 00:20:22,909
That's not the problem!

348
00:20:22,992 --> 00:20:25,328
There are gangsters outside. Gangsters!

349
00:20:25,620 --> 00:20:28,164
The gangsters are here to get you!

350
00:20:28,248 --> 00:20:29,249
Nam-il.

351
00:20:44,097 --> 00:20:45,473
Nam-il, get up.

352
00:20:45,557 --> 00:20:47,517
What? Uncle, are you off work already?

353
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:49,769
Gangsters are here! Get up, quick!

354
00:20:50,186 --> 00:20:51,187
Gangsters...

355
00:20:51,271 --> 00:20:52,772
Manager Bong, what are you doing?

356
00:20:54,107 --> 00:20:55,650
Hey, what's this?

357
00:20:56,484 --> 00:20:57,819
I'm sorry, sir. I...

358
00:20:58,319 --> 00:21:01,030
- I'll explain later. I'm sorry.
- Hey! What do you mean, later?

359
00:21:01,614 --> 00:21:02,907
Sir, I'll explain later.

360
00:21:03,116 --> 00:21:04,284
Hey!

361
00:21:04,951 --> 00:21:06,244
Hey! Get him!

362
00:21:18,047 --> 00:21:19,048
Get in, quick!

363
00:21:27,140 --> 00:21:28,141
- That way!
- Got it.

364
00:21:36,441 --> 00:21:38,860
Hey, stop right there!

365
00:21:39,110 --> 00:21:40,194
Hey! There's the bastard!

366
00:21:40,278 --> 00:21:41,571
Get him! Hey, hurry up!

367
00:21:43,281 --> 00:21:44,908
Go, get him!

368
00:21:45,867 --> 00:21:47,076
That hurts!

369
00:21:48,578 --> 00:21:49,579
Get him!

370
00:21:52,123 --> 00:21:53,541
Hey, stop!

371
00:21:55,585 --> 00:21:56,586
Wait, hold on.

372
00:22:02,508 --> 00:22:04,093
Hey, what's going on?

373
00:22:04,302 --> 00:22:06,095
Damn it!

374
00:22:12,644 --> 00:22:13,645
Oh no!

375
00:22:13,728 --> 00:22:17,649
Bensun! No.

376
00:22:17,899 --> 00:22:20,276
My Bensun!

377
00:22:22,445 --> 00:22:24,572
How many times do I have to tell you?

378
00:22:24,656 --> 00:22:25,949
I'll need to see your ID.

379
00:22:26,032 --> 00:22:28,159
I told you, I crossed on yellow.

380
00:22:28,534 --> 00:22:30,662
- Are you blind?
- Your ID, please.

381
00:22:30,787 --> 00:22:31,913
Gosh, seriously.

382
00:22:46,177 --> 00:22:47,178
Here you go.

383
00:22:50,098 --> 00:22:51,849
What a stuck-up bitch.

384
00:23:14,038 --> 00:23:15,206
- What the!
- You startled me.

385
00:23:15,581 --> 00:23:17,417
Oh, I'm sorry. I just...

386
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:18,918
you were standing out here in the rain.

387
00:23:19,919 --> 00:23:21,421
Oh, it was you.

388
00:23:21,963 --> 00:23:24,048
You have to give out tickets
even in weather like this?

389
00:23:24,590 --> 00:23:25,883
Yeah, pretty much.

390
00:23:25,967 --> 00:23:27,677
Here, please take this.

391
00:23:28,219 --> 00:23:30,138
- What about you?
- The bus drops me off

392
00:23:30,555 --> 00:23:31,931
right in front of my convenience store.

393
00:23:32,015 --> 00:23:34,058
You'll catch a cold if you stand
in the rain for too long.

394
00:23:34,142 --> 00:23:35,935
- That's my bus. I've gotta go.
- Oh, wait!

395
00:23:38,563 --> 00:23:40,606
Hey, wait a minute! Stop, stop!

396
00:23:40,690 --> 00:23:42,608
Hey! Sir, let me get on!

397
00:23:42,900 --> 00:23:44,277
Stop!

398
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:46,446
Sir, stop! Come on.

399
00:23:46,529 --> 00:23:48,114
I said stop! Please, stop!

400
00:24:00,418 --> 00:24:03,546
Get in. It's on my way.
I'll give you a ride.

401
00:24:05,423 --> 00:24:07,133
No, it's okay, really.

402
00:24:07,216 --> 00:24:08,885
It feels nice and cool. I'm fine.

403
00:24:08,968 --> 00:24:11,429
You know the buses here
only run once an hour, right?

404
00:24:12,388 --> 00:24:13,389
Get in.

405
00:24:15,141 --> 00:24:16,142
But I'm completely soaked.

406
00:24:16,225 --> 00:24:17,518
You're the one who said

407
00:24:17,602 --> 00:24:19,020
you'll catch a cold standing in the rain.

408
00:24:20,354 --> 00:24:21,397
It's fine.

409
00:24:28,488 --> 00:24:29,655
So...

410
00:24:30,490 --> 00:24:31,949
You're a fan of Chow Yun Fat, aren't you?

411
00:24:32,408 --> 00:24:34,535
Whoa! How did you know that?

412
00:24:34,619 --> 00:24:37,038
You popped up
on my "Friends You May Know" list.

413
00:24:37,705 --> 00:24:39,123
Your PFP is Chow Yun Fat, right?

414
00:24:39,373 --> 00:24:41,959
I'm a big fan of his too,
so I just thought I'd mention it.

415
00:24:42,210 --> 00:24:44,378
Wow, really? No way, I had no idea.

416
00:24:45,296 --> 00:24:46,589
Sorry, what's a "PFP"?

417
00:24:48,257 --> 00:24:49,634
Profile picture.

418
00:24:50,343 --> 00:24:51,427
Oh, the picture.

419
00:24:52,678 --> 00:24:53,846
Anyway, A Better Tomorrow...

420
00:24:53,930 --> 00:24:57,016
I remember watching that on VHS
when I was a kid. I loved it.

421
00:24:57,100 --> 00:24:58,101
Oh, right.

422
00:24:58,184 --> 00:25:00,019
A Better Tomorrow on VHS.

423
00:25:00,645 --> 00:25:02,271
It's a true masterpiece. You know...

424
00:25:03,231 --> 00:25:06,442
In that case,
you know A Better Tomorrow...

425
00:25:06,526 --> 00:25:09,237
is being rereleased
for its 40th anniversary, right?

426
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:10,530
Of course.

427
00:25:10,613 --> 00:25:12,198
Well, A Better Tomorrow is a movie that...

428
00:25:12,281 --> 00:25:13,866
is too much of a masterpiece

429
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,202
to be wasted on a small screen.

430
00:25:16,285 --> 00:25:18,871
So maybe, since this
opportunity came up...

431
00:25:18,955 --> 00:25:21,582
how about seeing it in a theater?

432
00:25:22,250 --> 00:25:23,251
Oh...

433
00:25:24,460 --> 00:25:26,587
I'd love to, but...

434
00:25:26,671 --> 00:25:28,840
I'm not a big fan

435
00:25:28,923 --> 00:25:30,675
of going to the movies by myself

436
00:25:31,384 --> 00:25:34,554
and I don't really have anyone to go with.

437
00:25:37,348 --> 00:25:39,058
Oh, I see.

438
00:25:39,517 --> 00:25:40,893
Oh, man. What to do?

439
00:25:42,812 --> 00:25:44,188
Well, in that case...

440
00:25:45,273 --> 00:25:47,150
at the movie theater...

441
00:25:48,609 --> 00:25:52,238
How about doing a
"going to the movies alone" challenge?

442
00:25:52,321 --> 00:25:54,991
You know those "eating alone" challenges?
It's been popular since the pandemic.

443
00:25:57,451 --> 00:25:59,745
- By myself?
- A lot of the younger crowd does it.

444
00:25:59,829 --> 00:26:01,664
By myself... Sure, I guess.

445
00:26:02,498 --> 00:26:04,333
- A challenge?
- A challenge. Be cool about it.

446
00:26:04,417 --> 00:26:05,960
Yeah, why not?

447
00:26:06,335 --> 00:26:11,048
JUMBO24
CONVENIENCE STORE

448
00:26:21,809 --> 00:26:23,227
Thank... Thank you.

449
00:26:23,811 --> 00:26:24,979
Thanks for the ride.

450
00:26:25,062 --> 00:26:26,480
You should get going. You must be busy.

451
00:26:26,731 --> 00:26:27,899
Okay.

452
00:26:28,733 --> 00:26:29,984
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes?

453
00:26:31,402 --> 00:26:33,029
A Better Tomorrow.

454
00:26:33,988 --> 00:26:35,198
When are you going to see it?

455
00:26:35,990 --> 00:26:37,950
It comes out the day after tomorrow

456
00:26:38,659 --> 00:26:39,869
- so I'm going on opening day.
- Really?

457
00:26:40,328 --> 00:26:41,871
- Yes.
- I happen to be

458
00:26:42,205 --> 00:26:43,289
off the day after tomorrow.

459
00:26:45,082 --> 00:26:47,335
Oh, really?

460
00:26:48,836 --> 00:26:52,256
Oh, do you guys work two shifts or three?
The police, I mean.

461
00:27:02,516 --> 00:27:04,518
- Do you want to go together?
- Go where?

462
00:27:07,063 --> 00:27:08,314
To the movies.

463
00:27:08,731 --> 00:27:09,982
A Better Tomorrow.

464
00:27:10,191 --> 00:27:11,484
I'm asking you to go see it with me.

465
00:27:16,572 --> 00:27:18,074
- You don't want to?
- No.

466
00:27:21,744 --> 00:27:22,745
I'd love to.

467
00:27:23,454 --> 00:27:25,331
Okay, I'll contact you about the time.

468
00:27:25,414 --> 00:27:26,415
Okay.

469
00:27:26,999 --> 00:27:28,542
- I'll be in touch.
- Okay.

470
00:27:43,224 --> 00:27:44,392
It doesn't hurt.

471
00:27:50,398 --> 00:27:51,607
- Come on.
- Yes, boss.

472
00:27:55,194 --> 00:27:57,571
Oh, are you all right? Boss, really...

473
00:27:57,905 --> 00:27:59,907
I have all my men searching for him.

474
00:27:59,991 --> 00:28:01,242
If you could just give me
a little more time...

475
00:28:01,325 --> 00:28:02,326
Hey, you son of a bitch.

476
00:28:02,410 --> 00:28:04,578
The deal our entire organization's future
depends on is the day after tomorrow

477
00:28:04,912 --> 00:28:05,955
and you want more time?

478
00:28:06,038 --> 00:28:08,332
If that Martial Arts Master shows up
and ruins the whole thing

479
00:28:08,416 --> 00:28:10,209
how can we go through with the deal

480
00:28:10,501 --> 00:28:12,253
when we don't even know
what that bastard is after?

481
00:28:13,879 --> 00:28:15,131
Boss, please.

482
00:28:15,464 --> 00:28:18,259
Wouldn't it be better
to just postpone the deal?

483
00:28:22,179 --> 00:28:25,141
You know how big the down payment is,
and you're still spouting that nonsense?

484
00:28:25,308 --> 00:28:27,476
If the deal falls through
and we end up with nothing

485
00:28:27,685 --> 00:28:29,645
- are you going to take responsibility?
- I'm sorry, sir.

486
00:28:30,021 --> 00:28:31,814
The deal is happening
no matter what. Got it?

487
00:28:31,897 --> 00:28:34,775
Before then, you catch that
Martial Arts Master and drag him to me.

488
00:28:34,942 --> 00:28:36,986
- Yes, sir.
- Drag him here!

489
00:28:37,069 --> 00:28:39,697
- Bring him to me!
- Yes, boss!

490
00:28:39,780 --> 00:28:40,865
Let's go.

491
00:28:44,493 --> 00:28:46,704
Damn, that hurts like hell.

492
00:28:48,539 --> 00:28:50,166
How long do I have to take this beating?

493
00:28:55,921 --> 00:28:57,506
Hey, Mr. Golden Boy.

494
00:28:59,133 --> 00:29:00,551
Oh, yes, Chairman. Hello.

495
00:29:02,011 --> 00:29:03,012
What's up, man?

496
00:29:03,387 --> 00:29:04,388
Why the long face?

497
00:29:04,472 --> 00:29:05,848
Something wrong?

498
00:29:06,557 --> 00:29:08,434
Oh, it's nothing.

499
00:29:08,517 --> 00:29:09,935
Oh, come on.

500
00:29:10,561 --> 00:29:11,562
Don't be like that.

501
00:29:11,645 --> 00:29:12,813
How about you and I...

502
00:29:12,897 --> 00:29:14,732
go for a drive in my supercar?

503
00:29:15,649 --> 00:29:17,068
With... with me?

504
00:29:17,151 --> 00:29:18,778
Yes. It's for you.

505
00:29:19,570 --> 00:29:20,571
Come on.

506
00:29:35,753 --> 00:29:36,879
Oh, I'm sorry.

507
00:29:38,005 --> 00:29:40,383
Just think of us as colleagues

508
00:29:40,466 --> 00:29:41,884
and let's be comfortable, okay?

509
00:29:41,967 --> 00:29:43,511
Here, have some coffee.

510
00:29:45,054 --> 00:29:46,222
Yeah, relax.

511
00:29:50,810 --> 00:29:52,436
Must be tough working
under President Yoo, huh?

512
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:53,521
No, not at all.

513
00:29:53,604 --> 00:29:54,897
Oh, come on.

514
00:29:55,898 --> 00:29:58,234
But for all the hard work you do

515
00:29:58,317 --> 00:29:59,485
it seems you're not treated very well.

516
00:29:59,568 --> 00:30:01,237
Your face is all banged up.

517
00:30:04,073 --> 00:30:07,284
I mean, if it were me,
for a great ace like our Mr. Geum

518
00:30:07,368 --> 00:30:09,954
I could make a much better offer.

519
00:30:12,998 --> 00:30:16,127
I have no intention of betraying my boss.

520
00:30:19,255 --> 00:30:20,464
Oh, I shouldn't have said that.

521
00:30:20,548 --> 00:30:21,632
Hey, hey, hey.

522
00:30:21,715 --> 00:30:24,260
Here, wipe the side
of your mouth. The coffee.

523
00:30:26,262 --> 00:30:29,849
I'm not trying to talk about something
as serious as betrayal. It's just...

524
00:30:30,766 --> 00:30:34,395
I wanted to chat with Mr. Geum
about the struggles at work.

525
00:30:35,604 --> 00:30:37,022
For example

526
00:30:37,314 --> 00:30:40,943
like the story
of the civilian who recently

527
00:30:41,026 --> 00:30:42,653
laid waste to Heaven Capital.

528
00:30:42,903 --> 00:30:46,115
Or what President Yoo
is secretly working on.

529
00:30:46,615 --> 00:30:49,243
Interesting topics
like his jerky business.

530
00:30:49,660 --> 00:30:50,661
Okay?

531
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:52,663
Chairman, how did you...

532
00:30:53,831 --> 00:30:54,874
Come on.

533
00:30:54,957 --> 00:30:56,375
There's no secret, man.

534
00:30:57,793 --> 00:30:58,794
Sorry?

535
00:31:00,629 --> 00:31:02,214
What... What did you say?

536
00:31:04,842 --> 00:31:07,428
I mean, there are no secrets.

537
00:31:07,970 --> 00:31:09,013
There are no secrets...

538
00:31:09,096 --> 00:31:10,973
CASHIER'S CHECK 10,000,000 WON

539
00:31:15,978 --> 00:31:17,938
The story our Mr. Geum told me today

540
00:31:18,022 --> 00:31:19,315
how should I put it...

541
00:31:20,024 --> 00:31:21,317
was so very moving.

542
00:31:21,525 --> 00:31:22,526
- Right.
- Let's...

543
00:31:22,610 --> 00:31:23,611
see each other again.

544
00:31:31,327 --> 00:31:33,078
- What do you want?
- It's a gift from the Chairman.

545
00:31:34,413 --> 00:31:35,456
A gift?

546
00:31:42,379 --> 00:31:43,589
Chairman, thank you.

547
00:31:51,805 --> 00:31:52,973
Oh, hello.

548
00:31:53,057 --> 00:31:54,183
Welcome.

549
00:31:54,266 --> 00:31:56,227
You must be coming
from the campaign trail.

550
00:31:56,310 --> 00:31:57,645
You're a little late today, aren't you?

551
00:31:57,728 --> 00:31:59,772
Yes, I suppose I am.

552
00:31:59,855 --> 00:32:01,774
Can I get a special
and a bottle of soju, please?

553
00:32:01,857 --> 00:32:03,692
Coming right up.

554
00:32:03,776 --> 00:32:04,985
Yes, goodness.

555
00:32:06,779 --> 00:32:07,780
Jeez.

556
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:20,834
Assemblyman Han, what are you doing here?

557
00:32:20,918 --> 00:32:23,462
I heard rumors that this is the spot

558
00:32:23,546 --> 00:32:25,214
Candidate Kim frequents every day

559
00:32:25,297 --> 00:32:26,549
so I came to see for myself.

560
00:32:28,092 --> 00:32:29,134
Am I making you uncomfortable?

561
00:32:29,677 --> 00:32:31,804
No, no, not at all.

562
00:32:31,887 --> 00:32:33,681
- Please, have a seat.
- Thank you.

563
00:32:34,848 --> 00:32:37,059
The gukbap here is out of this world.

564
00:32:37,142 --> 00:32:38,310
You should try it.

565
00:32:49,947 --> 00:32:50,948
Here.

566
00:32:51,448 --> 00:32:52,491
Let me pour you a drink.

567
00:32:53,826 --> 00:32:55,619
- Ah, thank you.
- Here.

568
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:02,001
Let me.

569
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:08,716
Oh, I'm sorry.

570
00:33:09,216 --> 00:33:11,677
I've been campaigning,
which isn't something I'm cut out for.

571
00:33:13,053 --> 00:33:15,264
When I was on my first campaign trail

572
00:33:15,764 --> 00:33:17,141
I shook so many hands

573
00:33:17,516 --> 00:33:18,934
that my hands were covered in blisters.

574
00:33:19,184 --> 00:33:21,020
Oh, really?

575
00:33:21,478 --> 00:33:24,064
Shaking hands all day
until my arm felt like it would fall off

576
00:33:24,148 --> 00:33:26,567
smiling until my face cramped up

577
00:33:26,650 --> 00:33:28,819
and giving speeches
until my voice was hoarse

578
00:33:29,778 --> 00:33:31,530
I couldn't help
but feel a sense of regret.

579
00:33:32,698 --> 00:33:35,826
"Did I really run for office
just for this?"

580
00:33:37,745 --> 00:33:39,330
How about you, Candidate Kim?

581
00:33:39,747 --> 00:33:40,956
Running in this election

582
00:33:41,540 --> 00:33:42,750
don't you regret it?

583
00:33:44,710 --> 00:33:47,212
For someone who has spent
their entire life as an educator

584
00:33:48,505 --> 00:33:50,591
playing the part of a politician
that doesn't suit you

585
00:33:51,216 --> 00:33:52,885
must be incredibly difficult.

586
00:33:53,969 --> 00:33:54,970
What if...

587
00:33:55,596 --> 00:33:57,556
the things you want to accomplish

588
00:33:58,182 --> 00:34:00,392
could be achieved
without you becoming mayor?

589
00:34:01,018 --> 00:34:03,395
Would you still continue
with the election?

590
00:34:09,193 --> 00:34:11,195
What are you trying to say?

591
00:34:26,293 --> 00:34:27,336
YEONGSEON ISLAND ORPHANAGE
SUPPORT PROJECT PROPOSAL

592
00:34:31,715 --> 00:34:33,926
COMMUNITY NETWORK, DEVELOPMENT AND
MANAGEMENT OF LOCAL RESOURCES...

593
00:34:37,304 --> 00:34:38,597
If you withdraw from the race...

594
00:34:39,765 --> 00:34:41,266
the orphanage on Yeongseon Island

595
00:34:41,350 --> 00:34:43,102
that you care so deeply about...

596
00:34:43,185 --> 00:34:44,478
the children there will also benefit.

597
00:34:45,229 --> 00:34:46,897
I hear their donations are so meager

598
00:34:46,980 --> 00:34:49,316
they can't even fix
the heating and cooling.

599
00:34:50,025 --> 00:34:52,486
But we could easily
build them a new building.

600
00:34:53,028 --> 00:34:54,697
Besides housing, we're also considering
a plan for scholarships.

601
00:34:55,364 --> 00:34:57,700
To allow the children to pursue the
education they want

602
00:34:57,783 --> 00:34:59,743
we are looking into ways
to provide support.

603
00:35:04,623 --> 00:35:06,041
I'm sorry

604
00:35:06,333 --> 00:35:08,001
but I'm going to pretend this
conversation never happened.

605
00:35:08,585 --> 00:35:10,796
I can't support the children

606
00:35:11,004 --> 00:35:12,840
with money from a questionable source.

607
00:35:14,758 --> 00:35:15,759
Source?

608
00:35:18,887 --> 00:35:21,056
Money is money.

609
00:35:21,140 --> 00:35:23,559
Even if you pour
your entire salary into it

610
00:35:23,976 --> 00:35:25,436
and volunteer every day...

611
00:35:26,645 --> 00:35:28,021
do you think you could accomplish

612
00:35:28,397 --> 00:35:30,149
even one thing on this plan?

613
00:35:31,024 --> 00:35:33,068
You said you'd make Yeongseon Island
a place for children.

614
00:35:33,819 --> 00:35:35,028
Were those all just empty words?

615
00:35:48,167 --> 00:35:49,877
You asked me

616
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:52,421
if I regretted running for office.

617
00:35:53,505 --> 00:35:54,506
Yes.

618
00:35:55,132 --> 00:35:56,550
It's a struggle every day.

619
00:35:57,468 --> 00:35:59,511
Every day, I want to run away.

620
00:36:01,138 --> 00:36:03,724
For someone like me
who's only ever been a teacher

621
00:36:04,558 --> 00:36:08,145
politics doesn't seem to be my calling.

622
00:36:08,812 --> 00:36:09,813
But...

623
00:36:10,105 --> 00:36:11,565
what's even scarier...

624
00:36:13,358 --> 00:36:15,486
is the thought of Assemblyman Han
becoming mayor

625
00:36:16,278 --> 00:36:19,865
ruining the island
and the children's futures

626
00:36:21,033 --> 00:36:22,493
and me just turning a blind eye to it.

627
00:36:29,917 --> 00:36:32,377
It seems this will be the last drink...

628
00:36:33,462 --> 00:36:34,797
we'll have together.

629
00:36:36,757 --> 00:36:38,759
Then order anything you'd like.

630
00:36:38,842 --> 00:36:39,843
Since it's our last

631
00:36:39,927 --> 00:36:41,053
it's on me.

632
00:36:41,428 --> 00:36:42,429
That's all right.

633
00:36:44,848 --> 00:36:45,849
CASHIER'S CHECK 100,000 WON

634
00:36:45,933 --> 00:36:47,267
I've had more than enough.

635
00:36:47,726 --> 00:36:48,727
Well, then.

636
00:36:55,984 --> 00:36:57,903
YEONGSEON ISLAND ORPHANAGE
SUPPORT PROJECT PROPOSAL

637
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:11,041
Hey, Joong-gi.

638
00:37:14,086 --> 00:37:15,420
It looks like I'll have to go do

639
00:37:16,672 --> 00:37:18,090
some volunteer work at the orphanage soon.

640
00:37:28,475 --> 00:37:30,185
If I go to Yeongseon Island now

641
00:37:30,936 --> 00:37:32,354
it'll mess up the whole plan.

642
00:37:38,443 --> 00:37:40,320
What are you talking about, Boss?

643
00:37:40,404 --> 00:37:42,865
Some prosecutor came for a visit.

644
00:37:43,532 --> 00:37:45,993
At first, I didn't know
what to make of it.

645
00:37:46,493 --> 00:37:50,038
Who knew she'd be some hard-ass
so fixated on that case?

646
00:37:54,751 --> 00:37:55,752
Beom-ryong.

647
00:37:55,836 --> 00:37:57,629
You need to go meet this Prosecutor Gang

648
00:37:58,130 --> 00:37:59,214
right away.

649
00:38:01,341 --> 00:38:03,552
Wait, are you telling me
to help a prosecutor?

650
00:38:03,635 --> 00:38:05,178
You think I enjoy working

651
00:38:05,262 --> 00:38:06,513
with some low-life prosecutor?

652
00:38:06,889 --> 00:38:08,181
Hey, but if it means

653
00:38:08,265 --> 00:38:09,349
I can clear my name

654
00:38:09,433 --> 00:38:11,935
and take down
that traitor bastard Yoo In-gu

655
00:38:12,394 --> 00:38:14,396
I suppose I can learn to love my enemy.

656
00:38:14,938 --> 00:38:17,733
I've already laid out the bait

657
00:38:17,941 --> 00:38:20,777
so Prosecutor Gang
is sure to approach Yoo In-gu.

658
00:38:21,278 --> 00:38:23,864
I need you to be proactive

659
00:38:24,364 --> 00:38:25,365
and help her.

660
00:38:25,699 --> 00:38:29,328
And start wrapping up your business.

661
00:38:30,037 --> 00:38:31,288
My... my business?

662
00:38:31,371 --> 00:38:32,915
But this could be our last chance.

663
00:38:32,998 --> 00:38:34,875
We have to risk our lives and go all in.

664
00:38:35,292 --> 00:38:36,710
We have to start gathering the boys

665
00:38:36,793 --> 00:38:38,754
and supporting this Prosecutor Gang.

666
00:38:38,879 --> 00:38:40,756
Do you think you'll have time
to run a business?

667
00:38:42,466 --> 00:38:43,467
Why?

668
00:38:43,550 --> 00:38:44,718
Is something holding you back?

669
00:39:10,452 --> 00:39:12,496
MASKED RACER LIVE ACTION PLAY
MASKED RACER'S GREAT ADVENTURE

670
00:39:13,372 --> 00:39:14,790
- What's this?
- You know...

671
00:39:14,873 --> 00:39:16,625
Ji-woo loves Masked Racer.

672
00:39:17,084 --> 00:39:18,627
They're putting on a show
at the Arts Center.

673
00:39:20,379 --> 00:39:22,047
What about the dinner service tomorrow?

674
00:39:24,049 --> 00:39:25,425
After Ji-woo was born

675
00:39:25,509 --> 00:39:28,720
we've been so busy,
we haven't had a proper outing.

676
00:39:28,804 --> 00:39:30,722
Let the three of us go,
get some fresh air for a change.

677
00:39:32,557 --> 00:39:33,767
Just go.

678
00:39:34,476 --> 00:39:36,520
Is it going to kill us to close
for a day or two?

679
00:39:36,728 --> 00:39:39,356
We can just close after the lunch service.

680
00:39:39,439 --> 00:39:40,565
Dad, even if we close
for one service, our sales...

681
00:39:40,691 --> 00:39:42,317
Forget about the sales!

682
00:39:42,818 --> 00:39:44,569
Do I have to walk on eggshells
running this place

683
00:39:44,653 --> 00:39:46,279
wondering if you two are fighting?

684
00:39:46,989 --> 00:39:49,199
Please, just go out and settle it already

685
00:39:49,282 --> 00:39:50,701
one way or another.

686
00:39:51,702 --> 00:39:55,372
Dad, it's not like
I was making things tense.

687
00:39:57,416 --> 00:39:59,418
All right, fine. We're going, okay?

688
00:40:00,002 --> 00:40:01,837
This is Ji-woo's favorite.

689
00:40:07,801 --> 00:40:09,720
Assemblyman Han, step down!

690
00:40:09,803 --> 00:40:13,098
- Step down! Step down!
- Step down! Step down!

691
00:40:13,181 --> 00:40:14,933
Chairman Do, step down!

692
00:40:15,017 --> 00:40:17,060
- Step down! Step down!
- Step down! Step down!

693
00:40:17,144 --> 00:40:18,520
- Step down!
- Step down!

694
00:40:41,126 --> 00:40:43,879
Oh, this is going to get ugly.

695
00:40:58,226 --> 00:40:59,352
Yes, this is Gang Yeong-ae.

696
00:40:59,436 --> 00:41:01,271
Going into the hotel right now...

697
00:41:01,605 --> 00:41:03,231
I suggest you think twice about it.

698
00:41:05,192 --> 00:41:06,485
Who are you, really?

699
00:41:14,159 --> 00:41:15,368
Are you stalking me?

700
00:41:15,452 --> 00:41:18,705
I'm not stalking you.
I'm trying to warn you. It's dangerous.

701
00:41:18,789 --> 00:41:21,458
Okay, so who are you
to keep giving me these warnings?

702
00:41:21,541 --> 00:41:23,960
- What, are we in a spy movie?
- Prosecutor Gang.

703
00:41:24,419 --> 00:41:27,172
I helped you lose the detective
that was tailing you.

704
00:41:27,255 --> 00:41:28,465
Don't you remember?

705
00:41:28,548 --> 00:41:30,634
- Just trust me.
- Okay.

706
00:41:32,677 --> 00:41:35,097
If you really want me to trust you,
come down to the prosecutor's office.

707
00:41:35,180 --> 00:41:36,848
I'll run a nice, thorough
background check on you

708
00:41:36,932 --> 00:41:39,559
and if you check out,
then I'll believe you.

709
00:41:42,521 --> 00:41:44,022
Go home now.

710
00:41:56,201 --> 00:41:57,202
Right.

711
00:41:57,536 --> 00:41:59,663
I'll think about it while I eat.

712
00:42:04,668 --> 00:42:06,169
You can eat at a time like this?

713
00:42:06,253 --> 00:42:07,462
Manager Lee, you're here.

714
00:42:07,546 --> 00:42:09,339
- Want an egg?
- No, I'm fine.

715
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:12,300
I brought as much of the stuff
the boss told me to throw out as I could.

716
00:42:17,973 --> 00:42:19,224
This is all you could grab?

717
00:42:19,891 --> 00:42:21,476
You could've tried harder.

718
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:23,478
Thanks. Thank you.

719
00:42:23,562 --> 00:42:24,688
When I go back to work

720
00:42:24,771 --> 00:42:27,524
I'll cover all your tasks. Thank you.

721
00:42:28,733 --> 00:42:30,110
I don't think that's going to happen.

722
00:42:32,154 --> 00:42:33,155
Manager Bong.

723
00:42:33,530 --> 00:42:36,158
Your employment was terminated,
effective today.

724
00:42:39,786 --> 00:42:41,204
No. I...

725
00:42:41,538 --> 00:42:43,290
Fired? But why?

726
00:42:43,373 --> 00:42:44,541
You really don't know?

727
00:42:45,500 --> 00:42:47,419
You constantly missed work

728
00:42:47,502 --> 00:42:49,421
you were secretly living at the office

729
00:42:49,504 --> 00:42:51,715
and you brought thugs
who wrecked the boss's car.

730
00:42:51,798 --> 00:42:53,675
The boss was about to
call the police on you

731
00:42:53,758 --> 00:42:55,385
for trespassing and a hit-and-run.

732
00:42:55,468 --> 00:42:58,013
I barely convinced him
not to press charges

733
00:42:58,096 --> 00:42:59,848
by agreeing to fire you
and deduct it from your severance.

734
00:42:59,931 --> 00:43:00,932
So...

735
00:43:04,311 --> 00:43:06,188
So, try not to feel like
this is too unfair.

736
00:43:07,105 --> 00:43:09,107
What? Uncle, you got fired?

737
00:43:09,941 --> 00:43:11,818
So are we completely broke now? Huh?

738
00:43:15,530 --> 00:43:17,449
Do you have anywhere to go?

739
00:43:17,908 --> 00:43:18,909
Does it look like it?

740
00:43:19,576 --> 00:43:21,953
There are thugs outside looking for us.

741
00:43:26,541 --> 00:43:27,542
Manager Bong.

742
00:43:28,001 --> 00:43:30,295
Do you just need a place
that provides room and board?

743
00:43:32,964 --> 00:43:36,051
I mean, I know a job
that provides room and board

744
00:43:36,134 --> 00:43:38,637
that I could introduce you to.

745
00:43:38,720 --> 00:43:40,430
But I'm not sure if you'd be good at it...

746
00:43:40,513 --> 00:43:42,891
I'll do it. Yeah, I'll definitely do it.

747
00:43:42,974 --> 00:43:44,476
I'll be great at it, no matter what.

748
00:43:44,851 --> 00:43:46,436
Cleaning, washing cars?

749
00:43:46,603 --> 00:43:47,771
What is it?

750
00:43:56,404 --> 00:43:58,573
D-DAY

751
00:44:03,203 --> 00:44:04,621
Excuse me.

752
00:44:05,372 --> 00:44:06,456
How can I help you?

753
00:44:08,375 --> 00:44:10,919
I'm Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae
from Imcheon District Prosecutors' Office.

754
00:44:11,002 --> 00:44:12,212
I'm here to see the president...

755
00:44:13,797 --> 00:44:14,798
Oh, my.

756
00:44:14,923 --> 00:44:17,509
You're Mr. Yoo In-gu, aren't you?

757
00:44:23,640 --> 00:44:26,893
A prosecutor, visiting a clean
and legitimate business like ours...

758
00:44:27,269 --> 00:44:28,645
what could possibly bring you here?

759
00:44:28,728 --> 00:44:30,814
Well, I...

760
00:44:31,189 --> 00:44:33,483
I'm currently investigating a case.

761
00:44:34,693 --> 00:44:36,111
And I have a few questions for you.

762
00:44:36,194 --> 00:44:37,404
Yes, of course.

763
00:44:43,702 --> 00:44:45,912
Do you happen to know anything

764
00:44:45,996 --> 00:44:48,456
about the Passenger Ship Spy Case
from ten years ago?

765
00:44:48,915 --> 00:44:50,083
That's the first I'm hearing of it.

766
00:44:50,166 --> 00:44:51,251
A spy came down here?

767
00:44:53,753 --> 00:44:54,754
Then...

768
00:44:55,338 --> 00:44:56,339
what about this?

769
00:44:56,715 --> 00:44:58,300
The case where your former boss,
Hwang Hwa-san

770
00:44:58,383 --> 00:45:00,176
murdered Kwon Soon-bok.

771
00:45:01,845 --> 00:45:04,097
Well, now. My memory's
a bit fuzzy on that.

772
00:45:04,180 --> 00:45:06,725
Didn't you take over the Hwasan Sect
and establish the Ingu Sect after that?

773
00:45:06,850 --> 00:45:07,851
Oh, I didn't take it over.

774
00:45:07,934 --> 00:45:09,102
I branched off on my own.

775
00:45:09,894 --> 00:45:11,771
And I don't know what these were about

776
00:45:11,855 --> 00:45:13,440
but what a tragedy.

777
00:45:13,523 --> 00:45:16,693
I don't really follow the news,
so I don't know much

778
00:45:17,193 --> 00:45:19,154
so I'm not sure how helpful
my answers can be.

779
00:45:19,988 --> 00:45:21,197
Shall we continue, though?

780
00:45:22,991 --> 00:45:25,535
Then I'll just ask you one last thing.

781
00:45:37,255 --> 00:45:38,423
You know who this is, right?

782
00:45:38,965 --> 00:45:40,425
Well, he's...

783
00:45:40,842 --> 00:45:43,094
Isn't he the one running for mayor?

784
00:45:43,553 --> 00:45:46,306
You don't watch the news, but you seem to
know Han Gyeong-wook quite well.

785
00:45:46,431 --> 00:45:48,016
I've just seen his campaign posters

786
00:45:48,099 --> 00:45:49,684
a few times.

787
00:45:50,226 --> 00:45:51,728
Let's be honest.

788
00:45:53,438 --> 00:45:55,106
These previous cases

789
00:45:55,190 --> 00:45:57,150
and Han Gyeong-wook...

790
00:45:57,567 --> 00:45:58,735
You know all about them, don't you?

791
00:45:58,818 --> 00:46:00,862
What, are you interrogating me now?

792
00:46:00,945 --> 00:46:02,447
Interrogating you? Me?

793
00:46:02,530 --> 00:46:04,115
I'm just asking you questions.

794
00:46:05,700 --> 00:46:07,118
Right, okay.

795
00:46:07,202 --> 00:46:08,661
In any case, as for the details...

796
00:46:08,828 --> 00:46:12,290
I'll hear them when I visit Han
Gyeong-wook in person.

797
00:46:12,499 --> 00:46:14,376
Wait, you're going to visit him in person?

798
00:46:15,210 --> 00:46:16,252
Oh, why?

799
00:46:16,336 --> 00:46:18,671
I mean, it's not like you know him.

800
00:46:19,255 --> 00:46:21,257
- So it shouldn't be a problem, right?
- Right. It's no problem.

801
00:46:24,803 --> 00:46:25,804
I see.

802
00:46:27,389 --> 00:46:28,598
Okay, got it.

803
00:46:29,182 --> 00:46:32,018
Well, thank you so much
for your cooperation.

804
00:46:32,102 --> 00:46:33,520
- Of course.
- Yes.

805
00:46:34,604 --> 00:46:36,314
Still, if by any chance...

806
00:46:36,398 --> 00:46:38,525
you remember anything...

807
00:46:38,733 --> 00:46:39,901
IMCHEON DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE
PROSECUTOR GANG YEONG-AE

808
00:46:40,610 --> 00:46:42,195
- Please give me a call.
- Sure.

809
00:46:42,278 --> 00:46:44,364
- Well, I'll be on my way.
- Yes, take care.

810
00:46:44,447 --> 00:46:45,907
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

811
00:46:54,707 --> 00:46:57,502
"He's a stranger."

812
00:46:58,253 --> 00:46:59,421
What a joke.

813
00:47:00,588 --> 00:47:02,132
IMCHEON DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE
PROSECUTOR GANG YEONG-AE

814
00:47:05,510 --> 00:47:06,511
Boss.

815
00:47:08,972 --> 00:47:10,223
Is she really a prosecutor?

816
00:47:10,306 --> 00:47:12,142
Why the hell is a prosecutor
showing up now, of all times?

817
00:47:14,686 --> 00:47:15,895
Hey, this is no time
to be standing around.

818
00:47:16,229 --> 00:47:19,315
- Have her tailed and report back to me.
- Yes, sir.

819
00:48:00,231 --> 00:48:01,232
TWO UNREAD MESSAGES

820
00:48:01,316 --> 00:48:02,609
OFFICER PARK MI-KYUNG
SEE YOU TOMORROW THEN!

821
00:48:02,692 --> 00:48:04,736
YOUR BOOKING IS COMPLETE
A BETTER TOMORROW

822
00:48:09,073 --> 00:48:10,450
A prosecutor from the Criminal Division
came to see him?

823
00:48:10,533 --> 00:48:11,534
Yes.

824
00:48:12,285 --> 00:48:15,121
I mean, everything the Ingu Sect
has ever done

825
00:48:15,205 --> 00:48:16,664
she just threw it all in the boss's face.

826
00:48:16,748 --> 00:48:18,249
As if she already knew everything.

827
00:48:20,210 --> 00:48:21,794
And on top of that, the real kicker was...

828
00:48:22,378 --> 00:48:24,172
she kept pressing him asking if he was

829
00:48:24,255 --> 00:48:25,256
connected to Chief Han.

830
00:48:25,340 --> 00:48:28,092
- Who? Chief Han?
- Yes.

831
00:48:29,427 --> 00:48:31,012
He was already worried
about Heaven Capital

832
00:48:31,095 --> 00:48:33,223
and terrified that
Chief Han would find out.

833
00:48:33,765 --> 00:48:36,142
And then a prosecutor
shows up out of the blue.

834
00:48:37,519 --> 00:48:39,562
In-gu is pretty much
losing his mind right now.

835
00:48:39,646 --> 00:48:40,897
He's so cornered

836
00:48:40,980 --> 00:48:42,607
he's ready to snap at
anyone who gets near him.

837
00:48:43,024 --> 00:48:44,108
Damn.

838
00:48:45,276 --> 00:48:47,654
This President Yoo is becoming
more and more of a problem.

839
00:48:48,655 --> 00:48:50,657
So, is President Yoo
just going to stand by

840
00:48:50,740 --> 00:48:52,116
and do nothing about that prosecutor?

841
00:48:54,035 --> 00:48:56,454
Come on, no matter how reckless the boss
gets

842
00:48:56,538 --> 00:48:58,414
you don't think he'd actually do
something to a prosecutor?

843
00:48:58,540 --> 00:49:01,417
I mean, you mess with one
and your life is over in a flash.

844
00:49:04,087 --> 00:49:05,129
Right?

845
00:49:05,630 --> 00:49:08,132
Mess with a prosecutor
and you're completely screwed.

846
00:49:17,892 --> 00:49:18,893
Yo!

847
00:49:20,103 --> 00:49:23,273
What the hell are you doing here
so early in the morning?

848
00:49:23,982 --> 00:49:25,525
There was something
I needed to check on urgently.

849
00:49:27,151 --> 00:49:29,904
It looks like a critical problem has come
up with Heaven Capital.

850
00:49:30,029 --> 00:49:33,032
- What's this punk up to now?
- A prosecutor...

851
00:49:33,908 --> 00:49:34,909
paid a visit.

852
00:49:35,535 --> 00:49:37,245
Looks like she got a whiff of what the
Ingu Sect's been doing

853
00:49:37,704 --> 00:49:39,038
and came sniffing around.

854
00:49:39,122 --> 00:49:40,248
How the hell would you know that?

855
00:49:40,331 --> 00:49:42,500
Because she came to me
and asked a bunch of questions.

856
00:49:42,584 --> 00:49:44,460
I played dumb
and said I didn't know anything

857
00:49:44,544 --> 00:49:45,962
but it was a tough spot to be in.

858
00:49:46,963 --> 00:49:48,881
I mean, now that a prosecutor's involved

859
00:49:48,965 --> 00:49:50,592
I can't just let this slide
without reporting

860
00:49:50,675 --> 00:49:51,968
such a serious matter to Chief Han.

861
00:49:52,051 --> 00:49:54,220
You son of a bitch,
are you going to snitch to Chief Han?

862
00:49:56,639 --> 00:49:57,682
What did you just call me?

863
00:50:01,019 --> 00:50:02,020
Hey.

864
00:50:02,103 --> 00:50:03,104
Yoo In-gu.

865
00:50:03,646 --> 00:50:06,357
You think I'm a pushover
just because I'm being nice?

866
00:50:07,150 --> 00:50:08,151
Do you?

867
00:50:08,985 --> 00:50:11,070
How dare you threaten me?

868
00:50:12,196 --> 00:50:13,865
Do you still not get it?

869
00:50:15,283 --> 00:50:16,326
What are you talking about?

870
00:50:16,868 --> 00:50:18,786
A prosecutor showed up! A prosecutor.

871
00:50:18,870 --> 00:50:20,246
Don't you know what that means?

872
00:50:21,247 --> 00:50:25,043
If she starts poking around Yeongseon
Island and blows our operation

873
00:50:25,126 --> 00:50:27,337
do you think Chief Han, with his temper,
will just stand by and watch?

874
00:50:27,420 --> 00:50:30,423
You, who caused this mess,
and me, who looked the other way...

875
00:50:31,716 --> 00:50:33,968
we'll both be killed without a trace.

876
00:50:34,719 --> 00:50:35,720
Got it?

877
00:50:37,013 --> 00:50:38,723
No, no.

878
00:50:38,806 --> 00:50:40,099
What was I thinking?

879
00:50:40,183 --> 00:50:42,644
Look, I'm sorry for getting angry.

880
00:50:42,810 --> 00:50:45,188
This is not good.
Before I get dragged down into this mess

881
00:50:45,271 --> 00:50:47,357
I think the right thing to do
is report this to Chief Han.

882
00:50:47,440 --> 00:50:49,609
- Chairman Do...
- Let go of me! Don't touch me.

883
00:50:49,692 --> 00:50:51,027
I didn't touch you!

884
00:50:51,110 --> 00:50:52,570
Come on, don't be like this.

885
00:50:52,654 --> 00:50:54,364
That prosecutor...

886
00:50:54,739 --> 00:50:57,033
I'll take care of her.
Just give me some time.

887
00:50:57,784 --> 00:51:01,621
What are you going to do if I give you
time? That's ridiculous.

888
00:51:01,704 --> 00:51:03,706
I have a way! I have a plan.

889
00:51:03,915 --> 00:51:04,916
I do.

890
00:51:04,999 --> 00:51:06,542
You said you trusted my abilities,
didn't you? Huh?

891
00:51:08,378 --> 00:51:09,545
You said we're in the same boat.

892
00:51:10,963 --> 00:51:13,257
Just give me some time,
and I'll handle it myself. I swear.

893
00:51:15,802 --> 00:51:17,136
Jesus Christ.

894
00:51:20,765 --> 00:51:21,849
You have one day.

895
00:51:21,933 --> 00:51:23,393
If you can't fix this by tomorrow

896
00:51:23,476 --> 00:51:26,437
then there's really nothing
I can do for you. Okay?

897
00:51:26,521 --> 00:51:28,773
- One day?
- One day. Yeah?

898
00:51:30,483 --> 00:51:32,402
Mr. Yoo. Don't keep...

899
00:51:33,069 --> 00:51:35,822
- making me be the bad guy. All right?
- Okay.

900
00:51:37,240 --> 00:51:39,033
- By tomorrow.
- Yeah, I got it.

901
00:51:48,501 --> 00:51:50,753
CLOSED FOR DINNER TONIGHT

902
00:51:51,087 --> 00:51:52,964
Ji-woo, what's this one's name?

903
00:51:53,256 --> 00:51:56,175
- Masked Racer.
- Oh, Masked Racer.

904
00:51:57,343 --> 00:51:59,011
Okay, then what about this guy?

905
00:51:59,679 --> 00:52:00,680
A monster.

906
00:52:02,181 --> 00:52:05,393
Gosh, you're a sharp judge of character.

907
00:52:08,146 --> 00:52:09,147
Mom.

908
00:52:29,709 --> 00:52:31,461
O-ran, you look amazing!

909
00:52:31,878 --> 00:52:33,337
Well, she takes after me

910
00:52:33,421 --> 00:52:36,174
so of course she's a knockout.
You know it.

911
00:52:37,175 --> 00:52:39,635
Mom, you look really pretty today.

912
00:52:42,180 --> 00:52:43,931
I just put on what I usually wear.

913
00:52:44,682 --> 00:52:46,100
Should I change if it's too much?

914
00:52:46,184 --> 00:52:47,643
No, it looks great on you.

915
00:52:48,227 --> 00:52:49,479
After the play

916
00:52:49,562 --> 00:52:50,813
let's go eat somewhere nice.

917
00:52:50,897 --> 00:52:52,023
I've already found a place.

918
00:52:53,107 --> 00:52:54,108
Let's go.

919
00:52:54,484 --> 00:52:56,277
- Ji-woo, let's go.
- Okay, have fun, sweetie.

920
00:52:56,360 --> 00:52:57,528
Let's go!

921
00:52:58,154 --> 00:52:59,530
- We'll get going.
- All right.

922
00:52:59,614 --> 00:53:01,616
- Have fun.
- We're off!

923
00:54:11,060 --> 00:54:14,146
IMCHEON DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE
PROSECUTOR GANG YEONG-AE

924
00:54:20,319 --> 00:54:22,572
- Hello?
- Prosecutor Gang Yeong-ae.

925
00:54:23,197 --> 00:54:24,574
Yes, speaking. Who is this?

926
00:54:24,657 --> 00:54:26,826
I used to serve Chairman Hwang Hwa-san.

927
00:54:26,993 --> 00:54:28,160
My name is Gang Beom-ryong.

928
00:54:28,953 --> 00:54:32,290
I was told you'd clear
our chairman's name.

929
00:54:33,291 --> 00:54:34,500
As much as I can

930
00:54:34,917 --> 00:54:36,127
I want to help you with that.

931
00:54:37,587 --> 00:54:38,838
Why should I...

932
00:54:38,921 --> 00:54:40,840
trust you, Mr. Gang Beom-ryong?

933
00:54:40,923 --> 00:54:42,091
Ten years ago...

934
00:54:42,675 --> 00:54:44,135
The Passenger Ship Spy Case.

935
00:54:45,678 --> 00:54:47,138
I was on that passenger ship.

936
00:54:47,638 --> 00:54:50,641
I know all the details of the case
you're interested in.

937
00:54:51,434 --> 00:54:53,227
You really know everything?

938
00:54:53,311 --> 00:54:55,354
I'd like to meet you
in person to tell you.

939
00:54:55,646 --> 00:54:57,023
Where are you right now, by any chance?

940
00:54:59,483 --> 00:55:01,611
- On Yeongseon Island.
- Yeongseon Island?

941
00:55:01,694 --> 00:55:03,321
Wait, Yoo In-gu...

942
00:55:05,656 --> 00:55:08,034
Have you already met Yoo In-gu?

943
00:55:08,242 --> 00:55:10,369
Yes, but it wasn't very fruitful.

944
00:55:10,453 --> 00:55:12,955
Let's meet somewhere quiet.

945
00:55:13,748 --> 00:55:15,124
I'll decide on the place.

946
00:55:19,211 --> 00:55:21,505
HAN GYEONG-WOOK! THE EXPERT FOR IMCHEON'S
CULTURE AND INDUSTRY

947
00:55:30,306 --> 00:55:31,974
- What brings you here?
- Well...

948
00:55:32,141 --> 00:55:34,268
I was hoping I could borrow some money.

949
00:55:34,977 --> 00:55:36,646
- Have a seat.
- Oh, okay.

950
00:55:48,616 --> 00:55:50,993
IOU LOAN AMOUNT 50,000 WON

951
00:55:51,786 --> 00:55:52,787
- Sir.
- Yes?

952
00:55:52,870 --> 00:55:54,789
- You wrote this part wrong.
- No, I didn't write it wrong.

953
00:55:54,872 --> 00:55:57,625
- No, I'm telling you, this is wrong.
- No, I didn't write it wrong.

954
00:55:59,710 --> 00:56:01,087
- Fifty thousand won?
- Yes, fifty thousand won.

955
00:56:01,587 --> 00:56:02,672
Fifty thousand won?

956
00:56:02,755 --> 00:56:05,216
Yes, fifty thousand won.
I'm on a roll right now, sir.

957
00:56:05,299 --> 00:56:07,301
So if I just pull the lever now,
I'll hit the jackpot.

958
00:56:07,385 --> 00:56:08,469
- Get out.
- No, sir.

959
00:56:08,552 --> 00:56:10,680
- I said, get out.
- No. I really need this. I...

960
00:56:10,763 --> 00:56:12,306
- Hey, guys! Hey!
- Jackpot.

961
00:56:12,390 --> 00:56:13,724
- Hey, get him out of here! Now!
- I'm about to hit the jackpot!

962
00:56:13,808 --> 00:56:15,643
I swear, my time has come!

963
00:56:15,726 --> 00:56:17,853
- Are you kidding me? Damn.
- No, I...

964
00:56:17,937 --> 00:56:19,021
Hey.

965
00:56:19,105 --> 00:56:21,107
- Just 50,000 won.
- Knock some sense into him. Seriously.

966
00:56:21,190 --> 00:56:22,900
Just 50,000 won. I'm telling you.

967
00:56:22,984 --> 00:56:25,569
I'm on a roll! Just 50,000 won!

968
00:56:37,123 --> 00:56:38,124
Boss.

969
00:56:38,207 --> 00:56:39,208
What should we do?

970
00:56:40,835 --> 00:56:42,169
Where's the prosecutor?

971
00:56:43,671 --> 00:56:45,631
She's snooping around Yeongseon Island

972
00:56:45,715 --> 00:56:47,633
digging into Heaven Capital.

973
00:56:49,385 --> 00:56:50,928
Boss, you shouldn't.

974
00:56:51,554 --> 00:56:52,555
Let's postpone

975
00:56:53,014 --> 00:56:54,181
the drug deal.

976
00:56:55,975 --> 00:56:58,769
Do you have any idea how hard it was to
get this supplier?

977
00:56:59,103 --> 00:57:01,230
I put all of the Ingu Sect's
money into this.

978
00:57:01,814 --> 00:57:03,482
If this deal falls through,
we're bankrupt.

979
00:57:03,566 --> 00:57:05,026
But what if...

980
00:57:05,109 --> 00:57:07,820
What if that prosecutor bitch
gets a whiff of the drugs?

981
00:57:07,903 --> 00:57:10,781
What if things go wrong
and Chief Han finds out?

982
00:57:12,366 --> 00:57:14,535
This is on a whole different level
than the Martial Arts Master problem.

983
00:57:14,660 --> 00:57:16,203
There's no going back from this, Boss.

984
00:57:17,329 --> 00:57:18,539
Either way...

985
00:57:19,123 --> 00:57:21,792
If the deal falls through,
the Chinese won't let it slide.

986
00:57:22,126 --> 00:57:24,378
And if we don't deal
with the prosecutor by today

987
00:57:24,462 --> 00:57:27,423
that fox Chairman Do
will tattle to Chief Han.

988
00:57:27,715 --> 00:57:30,760
Whether we die because the deal is off,
or at the hands of Chief Han

989
00:57:31,052 --> 00:57:32,470
we die either way.

990
00:57:32,553 --> 00:57:34,597
Jeez, then what do we do?

991
00:57:35,139 --> 00:57:36,640
No matter how I think about it

992
00:57:37,016 --> 00:57:38,350
there's only one way to survive.

993
00:57:43,105 --> 00:57:44,106
The prosecutor...

994
00:57:45,316 --> 00:57:46,984
- Let's take her out.
- What?

995
00:57:48,778 --> 00:57:49,945
Boss.

996
00:57:50,529 --> 00:57:52,823
Going after a prosecutor
will blow this whole thing up.

997
00:57:52,907 --> 00:57:55,326
We can dump her in the ocean
without a soul knowing.

998
00:57:55,576 --> 00:57:58,037
We can bribe the Yeongseon Island cops
to erase any trace.

999
00:57:58,120 --> 00:58:00,414
- But still...
- If the prosecutor disappears

1000
00:58:00,831 --> 00:58:01,832
everything's clean.

1001
00:58:02,083 --> 00:58:04,085
We can deal with
the Martial Arts Master after that.

1002
00:58:04,168 --> 00:58:05,544
Damn it.

1003
00:58:05,669 --> 00:58:06,962
Kang-sik, you stop yapping

1004
00:58:07,046 --> 00:58:08,631
and get some of your best guys ready.

1005
00:58:09,048 --> 00:58:11,092
When the time is right, we'll do the job.

1006
00:58:11,383 --> 00:58:13,844
Damn it, I knew this was going
to cause trouble.

1007
00:58:18,808 --> 00:58:21,352
RESTRICTED NUMBER

1008
00:58:24,146 --> 00:58:25,189
RESTRICTED NUMBER

1009
00:58:56,345 --> 00:59:03,144
HILLSIDE CAFE

1010
00:59:19,869 --> 00:59:21,787
Yes. I've arrived.

1011
00:59:22,246 --> 00:59:24,123
She just went into
the Hillside Cafe in Nakwon-ri.

1012
00:59:24,206 --> 00:59:25,541
Hill... Hillside Cafe?

1013
00:59:25,666 --> 00:59:27,042
Hillside Cafe.

1014
00:59:28,169 --> 00:59:29,920
HILLSIDE CAFE

1015
00:59:31,005 --> 00:59:32,006
Twenty minutes.

1016
00:59:43,309 --> 00:59:44,727
Answer the phone.

1017
00:59:46,395 --> 00:59:48,022
This is driving me crazy.

1018
00:59:48,105 --> 00:59:49,523
Why isn't she answering?

1019
00:59:51,567 --> 00:59:53,694
Answer the phone... Damn it.

1020
01:00:00,701 --> 01:00:03,204
The number you have dialed is unavailable.
Please leave a message...

1021
01:00:42,493 --> 01:00:44,495
This is driving me crazy.

1022
01:00:58,050 --> 01:01:00,261
Taxi!

1023
01:01:00,636 --> 01:01:01,845
Hey!

1024
01:01:13,857 --> 01:01:15,150
Oh, look. We're next.

1025
01:01:15,234 --> 01:01:17,027
MASKED RACER

1026
01:01:17,611 --> 01:01:19,071
Hey, want to take one with Mom?

1027
01:01:19,196 --> 01:01:21,240
Come on, what is with you?

1028
01:01:21,365 --> 01:01:22,366
Ji-woo, what pose should we do?

1029
01:01:22,449 --> 01:01:24,285
I'll, um... I'll do this.

1030
01:01:24,368 --> 01:01:25,869
All right, let's go.

1031
01:01:26,370 --> 01:01:28,247
Hey, I'm gonna run to the restroom.

1032
01:01:28,330 --> 01:01:29,456
- Okay, go ahead.
- I'll be back.

1033
01:01:29,540 --> 01:01:30,708
Let's go, Ji-woo.

1034
01:01:31,166 --> 01:01:33,585
MASKED RACER

1035
01:01:34,128 --> 01:01:35,504
Ready to strike a pose, buddy?

1036
01:01:35,587 --> 01:01:37,881
- Like this?
- Wow, you're a natural.

1037
01:01:39,008 --> 01:01:41,176
Okay, one, two, three.

1038
01:01:43,262 --> 01:01:44,805
RESTRICTED NUMBER

1039
01:01:48,392 --> 01:01:49,560
Want to take one more, buddy?

1040
01:01:49,643 --> 01:01:51,312
Sorry about that. I messed up the shot.

1041
01:01:52,479 --> 01:01:54,440
Why are you calling?
And from a regular phone?

1042
01:01:54,523 --> 01:01:57,109
Ho-myeong, it's an emergency.
Get over here now.

1043
01:01:57,192 --> 01:01:58,777
What are you talking about?
Damn it, I can't.

1044
01:01:58,861 --> 01:02:00,279
I'm with my family at a show.

1045
01:02:00,362 --> 01:02:01,780
Listen, Yoo In-gu's crew

1046
01:02:01,864 --> 01:02:04,283
is going to take out Prosecutor Gang.

1047
01:02:04,533 --> 01:02:05,534
What did you say?

1048
01:02:06,118 --> 01:02:08,037
- Where are you right now?
- I'm on Yeongseon Island.

1049
01:02:08,162 --> 01:02:10,039
Prosecutor Gang
is on Yeongseon Island now?

1050
01:02:10,122 --> 01:02:11,123
Yeah.

1051
01:02:11,540 --> 01:02:13,125
Prosecutor Gang...

1052
01:02:13,208 --> 01:02:16,128
provoked Yoo In-gu,
and now that crazy bastard...

1053
01:02:16,795 --> 01:02:19,715
Look, I don't have time to explain.
Just get over here. Hurry!

1054
01:02:20,966 --> 01:02:22,051
This is driving me crazy, damn it.

1055
01:02:22,134 --> 01:02:24,595
If you don't come,
Prosecutor Gang is going to die, man.

1056
01:02:27,765 --> 01:02:28,974
But what's wrong with your voice?

1057
01:02:29,058 --> 01:02:30,517
It's nothing. I'm fine.

1058
01:02:30,601 --> 01:02:32,478
I'm just a little hurt. Now, hurry up.

1059
01:02:33,354 --> 01:02:35,606
If Prosecutor Gang goes down,
it's all over.

1060
01:02:36,148 --> 01:02:37,566
Ho-myeong, get here fast.

1061
01:02:41,737 --> 01:02:43,113
All right. I'll call you back.

1062
01:02:47,201 --> 01:02:48,202
Dad.

1063
01:02:49,578 --> 01:02:51,372
Do you have to go save the day?

1064
01:02:54,666 --> 01:02:56,877
Masked Racer always has to...

1065
01:02:57,086 --> 01:03:00,214
leave right when he's having fun.

1066
01:03:03,675 --> 01:03:07,096
But you're going off
to fight the bad guys.

1067
01:03:07,179 --> 01:03:08,389
So I'm okay.

1068
01:03:13,685 --> 01:03:14,853
Ji-woo.

1069
01:03:18,565 --> 01:03:20,609
The show will be starting shortly.

1070
01:03:20,692 --> 01:03:21,777
It's starting. Let's go.

1071
01:03:21,860 --> 01:03:24,780
We ask all audience members
to please enter the theater.

1072
01:03:33,122 --> 01:03:34,540
Hey, listen.

1073
01:03:35,332 --> 01:03:36,333
Well...

1074
01:03:37,084 --> 01:03:38,335
About the show...

1075
01:03:39,294 --> 01:03:40,295
Do you...

1076
01:03:41,422 --> 01:03:42,423
Do you think

1077
01:03:42,506 --> 01:03:44,800
- you could watch without me for a bit?
- What?

1078
01:03:46,301 --> 01:03:48,220
- What are you talking about?
- It's just...

1079
01:03:49,012 --> 01:03:51,265
something urgent came up.
I have to go take care of it.

1080
01:03:53,767 --> 01:03:56,478
What is it? Did the shop catch on fire?

1081
01:03:56,812 --> 01:03:58,355
What could be so urgent?

1082
01:03:58,439 --> 01:03:59,731
I'll explain when I get back.

1083
01:03:59,940 --> 01:04:01,316
I'm sorry. It's a real emergency.

1084
01:04:01,400 --> 01:04:04,236
So you can't even tell me what it is

1085
01:04:05,237 --> 01:04:06,780
but you have to leave for this emergency?

1086
01:04:06,864 --> 01:04:07,865
Mom.

1087
01:04:07,948 --> 01:04:09,616
I'm okay if we just watch it together.

1088
01:04:12,953 --> 01:04:15,080
Go save the day!

1089
01:04:16,290 --> 01:04:18,667
- I can't believe you.
- Mom, the show's starting.

1090
01:04:19,001 --> 01:04:20,085
Let's go watch.

1091
01:04:20,627 --> 01:04:21,628
Dad, go on.

1092
01:04:21,879 --> 01:04:23,797
I'm going to go watch the show with Mom.

1093
01:04:23,881 --> 01:04:26,925
Ji-woo, let me just
talk to your dad for a second.

1094
01:04:27,801 --> 01:04:28,927
I'm so sorry.

1095
01:04:29,052 --> 01:04:30,596
O-ran. Ji-woo.

1096
01:04:30,846 --> 01:04:32,473
I'll be back...

1097
01:04:32,723 --> 01:04:34,016
really soon.

1098
01:04:34,224 --> 01:04:35,684
Hey, wait.

1099
01:04:35,767 --> 01:04:36,977
Mom.

1100
01:04:38,437 --> 01:04:39,521
Wait...

1101
01:04:51,325 --> 01:04:54,119
HILLSIDE CAFE

1102
01:05:02,419 --> 01:05:03,462
Excuse me.

1103
01:05:03,962 --> 01:05:05,422
What happened here?

1104
01:05:05,797 --> 01:05:06,965
Don't even ask.

1105
01:05:07,174 --> 01:05:08,300
A while ago

1106
01:05:08,383 --> 01:05:09,801
some thugs stormed in here

1107
01:05:09,885 --> 01:05:11,887
trying to get a woman.

1108
01:05:12,137 --> 01:05:14,014
They totally wrecked the place.

1109
01:05:14,515 --> 01:05:15,766
Damn it.

1110
01:05:17,643 --> 01:05:19,102
Where did they all go?

1111
01:05:19,228 --> 01:05:20,229
I don't know.

1112
01:05:20,521 --> 01:05:21,980
They just sped off in a car.

1113
01:05:22,356 --> 01:05:23,357
Which way did they go?

1114
01:05:23,440 --> 01:05:24,775
They headed toward the main road.

1115
01:05:29,196 --> 01:05:30,239
Thank you.

1116
01:06:00,018 --> 01:06:02,980
SPECIAL THANKS TO OUR GUEST STARS
KIM SANG-KYUNG, KWON YUL, AND PARK JI-HWAN

1117
01:06:17,494 --> 01:06:18,495
Let's go together.

1118
01:06:18,579 --> 01:06:20,497
Han Gyeong-wook
and Yoo In-gu are connected.

1119
01:06:21,164 --> 01:06:22,874
They crashed into the Yeongseon River.
Are they dead?

1120
01:06:22,958 --> 01:06:24,334
If they're lucky,
they might have survived.

1121
01:06:24,418 --> 01:06:26,128
- Excuse me.
- I've got a bad feeling about this.

1122
01:06:26,211 --> 01:06:27,754
- Is he a criminal?
- You said you're Bong Je-sun, right?

1123
01:06:27,838 --> 01:06:30,257
The poor sap who lost
your home and got fired.

1124
01:06:30,966 --> 01:06:33,468
Have you been spying
on Jeong Ho-myeong lately?

1125
01:06:33,552 --> 01:06:34,928
What on earth are you hiding from me?

1126
01:06:35,012 --> 01:06:38,307
- Sir, are you sure nothing's wrong?
- I got kicked out.

1127
01:06:38,390 --> 01:06:40,475
How about we bring in a new member?

1128
01:06:40,559 --> 01:06:42,603
- I'll do my best.
- I'll give it a shot.

1129
01:06:42,728 --> 01:06:44,396
That's complete nonsense.

1130
01:06:44,479 --> 01:06:46,106
As an agent
for the National Intelligence Service

1131
01:06:46,189 --> 01:06:48,191
how could you team up with a thug?

